WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.429
{"en":"--- lesson 11  Not guilty ","ch":"无罪 "}

2
00:00:03.579 --> 00:00:07.112
{"en":"Customs Officers are quite tolerant these days, ^ ","ch":"现在的海关官员往往相当宽容。  "}

3
00:00:07.262 --> 00:00:13.042
{"en":"but they can still stop you when you are going through the Green Channel and have nothing to declare. ^ ","ch":"但是， 当你通过绿色通道， 没有任何东西需要申报时， 他们仍可以拦住你。  "}

4
00:00:13.192 --> 00:00:17.587
{"en":"Even really honest people are often made to feel guilty. ^ ","ch":"甚至是最诚实的人也常弄得觉得有罪似的，  "}

5
00:00:17.737 --> 00:00:28.637
{"en":"The hardened professional smuggler,  on the other hand,  is never troubled by such feelings,  even if he has five hundred gold watches hidden in his suitcase. ^ ","ch":"而老练的职业走私犯却即使在手提箱里藏着500只金表， 却也处之泰然。  "}

6
00:00:28.787 --> 00:00:37.362
{"en":"When I returned from abroad recently,  a particularly officious young Customs Officer clearly regarded me as a smuggler. ^ ","ch":"最近一次， 我也出国归来， 碰上一位特别好管闲事的年轻海关官员， 他显然把我当成了走私犯。  "}

7
00:00:37.512 --> 00:00:43.109
{"en":"'Have you anything to declare? ' he asked,  looking me in the eye. ^ “","ch":"您有什么需要申报的吗? ”他直盯着我的眼睛问。  "}

8
00:00:43.259 --> 00:00:46.557
{"en":"'No, ' I answered confidently. ^ “","ch":"没有。 ”我自信地回答说。  "}

9
00:00:46.707 --> 00:00:50.162
{"en":"'Would you mind unlocking this suitcase please? '^ “","ch":"请打开这只手提箱好吗? ” "}

10
00:00:50.312 --> 00:00:52.826
{"en":"'Not at all, ' I answered. ^ “","ch":"好的。 ”我回答说。  "}

11
00:00:52.976 --> 00:00:56.483
{"en":"The Officer went through the case with great care. ^ ","ch":"那位官员十分仔细地把箱子检查了一遍。  "}

12
00:00:56.633 --> 00:01:02.283
{"en":"All the things I had packed so carefully were soon in a dreadful mess. ^ ","ch":"所有细心包装好的东西一会儿工夫就乱成一团。  "}

13
00:01:02.433 --> 00:01:06.828
{"en":"I felt sure I would never be able to close the case again. ^ ","ch":"我相信那箱子再也关不上了。  "}

14
00:01:06.978 --> 00:01:10.825
{"en":"Suddenly,  I saw the Officer's face light up. ^ ","ch":"突然， 我看到官员脸上露出了得意的神色。  "}

15
00:01:10.975 --> 00:01:17.643
{"en":"He had spotted a tiny bottle at the bottom of my case and he pounced on it with delight. ^ ","ch":"他在我的箱底发现了一只小瓶， 高兴地一把抓了起来。  "}

16
00:01:17.793 --> 00:01:22.632
{"en":"'Perfume,  eh? ' he asked sarcastically. ^ “","ch":"香水， 嗯? ”他讥讽地说道，  "}

17
00:01:22.782 --> 00:01:28.954
{"en":"'You should have declared that.  Perfume is not exempt from import duty. '^ “","ch":"你刚才应该申报， 香水要上进口税的。 ” "}

18
00:01:29.104 --> 00:01:33.003
{"en":"'But it isn't perfume, ' I said. ^ “","ch":"不， 这不是香水， ”我说，  "}

19
00:01:33.153 --> 00:01:37.156
{"en":"'It's hair gel. ' Then I added with a smile, ^ “","ch":"是发胶。 ”接着我脸带微笑补充说： "}

20
00:01:37.306 --> 00:01:40.604
{"en":"'It's a strange mixture I make myself. '^ “","ch":"这是一种我自己配制的奇特的混合物。 ” "}

21
00:01:40.754 --> 00:01:44.261
{"en":"As I expected,  he did not believe me. ^ ","ch":"果不出所料， 他并不相信我。  "}

22
00:01:44.411 --> 00:01:47.840
{"en":"'Try it! ' I said encouragingly. ^ “","ch":"你就闻一闻吧！ ”我催促说。  "}

23
00:01:47.990 --> 00:01:52.542
{"en":"The officer unscrewed the cap and put the bottle to his nostrils. ^ ","ch":"海关官员拧开瓶盖， 把瓶子放到鼻子底下。  "}

24
00:01:52.692 --> 00:01:58.681
{"en":"He was greeted by an unpleasant smell which convinced him that I was telling the truth. ^ ","ch":"一股怪味袭来， 使他相信了我说的真话。  "}

25
00:01:58.831 --> 00:02:05.656
{"en":"A few minutes later,  I was able to hurry away with precious chalk marks on my baggage. ^ ","ch":"几分钟后， 我终于被放行， 手提划着宝贵的粉笔记号的行李， 匆匆离去。  "}

